WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.586 --> 00:00:02.960
MALE SPEAKER: My
friends, I am so

00:00:02.960 --> 00:00:06.270
happy to have our
friends here, Dr. Ari

00:00:06.270 --> 00:00:07.660
and Walter-- Walter Link.

00:00:07.660 --> 00:00:12.780
Dr. Ari is the
founder Sarvodaya.

00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:17.550
Sarvodaya is Sri Lanka's
largest social movement.

00:00:17.550 --> 00:00:21.560
Dr. Ari is widely known as
the Gandhi of Sri Lanka.

00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:26.530
And in my opinion, Dr. Ari can
be described in just two words,

00:00:26.530 --> 00:00:30.220
and the two words
are living saint.

00:00:30.220 --> 00:00:32.900
He's a humble
English teacher who

00:00:32.900 --> 00:00:35.770
through the sheer
force of his goodness

00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:40.330
created the largest social
movement in Sri Lanka involving

00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:43.270
15,000 villages,
millions of people,

00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:46.510
building thousand of schools,
health centers, libraries,

00:00:46.510 --> 00:00:50.320
roads, and village
banks, and so on.

00:00:50.320 --> 00:00:54.790
Dr. Ari demonstrates that you
can integrate deep in the work

00:00:54.790 --> 00:01:02.380
with transforming every aspect
of human life and the world.

00:01:02.380 --> 00:01:06.610
Walter here is a close friend
of Dr. Ari and his family.

00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:08.282
He chairs--

00:01:08.282 --> 00:01:09.990
DR. WALTER LINK:
Sarvodaya International.

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:13.060
MALE SPEAKER: Sarvodaya
international.

00:01:13.060 --> 00:01:16.710
And as Senior Strategy
Advisor and a leadership coach

00:01:16.710 --> 00:01:20.340
and associate investment
banker to the organization,

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:23.960
Walter is involved in
the same kind of work.

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:28.190
His work is integration of
personal personal practice

00:01:28.190 --> 00:01:30.029
into the broader world.

00:01:30.029 --> 00:01:32.570
My friends, please give a warm
welcome to Dr. Ari and Walter.

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:40.830
Let's begin, since
we have a saint here,

00:01:40.830 --> 00:01:43.280
let's begin with
some saintly sitting.

00:01:43.280 --> 00:01:45.000
I'm going to invite
Dr. Ari to guide us

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:47.870
in a few minutes
of mindful sitting,

00:01:47.870 --> 00:01:49.480
and then I'll have
Walter guide us

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:52.979
a few minutes of
relationship practice.

00:01:52.979 --> 00:01:54.270
DR. A.T. ARIYARATNE: Thank you.

00:01:57.490 --> 00:02:04.100
I'm extremely delighted that I'm
able to receive Google again.

00:02:06.940 --> 00:02:14.410
Google I remembered because
of this jolly good fellow who

00:02:14.410 --> 00:02:19.620
cannot be erased from my
mind from the day I met him.

00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:25.200
What we need is human
beings on this planet who

00:02:25.200 --> 00:02:36.420
can live all the time
in I call joy of living.

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:37.645
He's one such person.

00:02:40.650 --> 00:02:51.290
I'm very humbled to be
back with you and Google,

00:02:51.290 --> 00:02:58.360
and I'm looking forward to
greater universal service

00:02:58.360 --> 00:03:03.020
on the part of the institution
as well as all of you.

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:07.210
To anything in the
world, mind is supreme.

00:03:07.210 --> 00:03:10.020
Therefore, for a
moment, let us try

00:03:10.020 --> 00:03:16.122
to develop some
mindfulness by undergoing

00:03:16.122 --> 00:03:19.062
a few minutes of meditation.

00:03:19.062 --> 00:03:23.635
Please close your
eyes very lightly.

00:03:23.635 --> 00:03:26.155
Keep your feet on the ground.

00:03:29.386 --> 00:03:40.200
Keep the back erect so that the
nose, the chin, and the chest,

00:03:40.200 --> 00:03:42.456
fall in one line.

00:03:42.456 --> 00:03:45.420
Keep the right hand
on the left hand.

00:03:50.810 --> 00:03:55.550
Just look at your own body.

00:03:58.630 --> 00:04:01.690
Head to foot.

00:04:01.690 --> 00:04:10.885
Normally, we do not look
at our body with our mind.

00:04:13.540 --> 00:04:20.529
Now let us look at
our body and see

00:04:20.529 --> 00:04:26.570
how this body is nothing
but getting together

00:04:26.570 --> 00:04:31.910
of all elements in nature.

00:04:31.910 --> 00:04:32.410
Hardness.

00:04:35.260 --> 00:04:35.760
Liquidity.

00:04:38.550 --> 00:04:41.360
Air or expandability
or contractability.

00:04:44.110 --> 00:04:44.750
And heat.

00:04:50.290 --> 00:04:56.100
These are the four elements
that go to make my body.

00:04:56.100 --> 00:05:02.620
Similarly, all of us are
made of these four elements

00:05:02.620 --> 00:05:05.180
and everything around
us and in the world.

00:05:11.190 --> 00:05:18.070
Now we slowly bring our mind
to the tip of the nostrils.

00:05:22.020 --> 00:05:28.420
I observe how the breath
enters through the nostrils.

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:34.105
How they escape
through the nostrils.

00:05:37.320 --> 00:05:40.100
Sometimes short breaths.

00:05:40.100 --> 00:05:43.670
Sometimes long breaths.

00:05:43.670 --> 00:05:45.690
Sometimes through one nostril.

00:05:45.690 --> 00:05:47.010
Sometimes through both.

00:05:49.600 --> 00:06:01.020
For a moment let us observe how
this breath coming in and out

00:06:01.020 --> 00:06:02.150
conducts itself.

00:06:45.010 --> 00:06:54.470
While trying to concentrate our
mind to breathing in and out,

00:06:54.470 --> 00:07:00.540
we feel very relaxed in
body as well as the mind.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:10.650
How does the mind originate?

00:07:10.650 --> 00:07:20.170
We have in this body,
living body, a pair of eyes,

00:07:20.170 --> 00:07:24.640
a pair of ears, a
nose, a tongue, a body,

00:07:24.640 --> 00:07:28.260
as well as a mind.

00:07:43.140 --> 00:07:48.650
But through images that
fall into our eyes,

00:07:48.650 --> 00:07:50.340
eye consciousness is created.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:57.940
Similarly, sounds create
sound consciousness.

00:08:01.320 --> 00:08:10.830
Smell creates olfactory,
all smell consciousness.

00:08:14.400 --> 00:08:17.183
Tongue creates
taste consciousness.

00:08:20.970 --> 00:08:26.146
Body creates feelings.

00:08:28.970 --> 00:08:31.120
Mind creates thoughts, memories.

00:08:33.690 --> 00:08:39.413
All these six sensations,
senses, create sensations.

00:08:42.289 --> 00:08:48.220
Now, while keeping the mind
in breathing in and out,

00:08:48.220 --> 00:08:59.860
we try to observe how these
six sensory organs get messages

00:08:59.860 --> 00:09:08.850
from outside, creating either
pleasant feelings and thoughts

00:09:08.850 --> 00:09:16.160
or creating unpleasant or even
neutral thoughts and feelings.

00:09:19.360 --> 00:09:23.820
Observe the six
sensory organs and how

00:09:23.820 --> 00:09:30.240
they behave while keeping
the mind always breathing

00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:32.383
in and out at the
starting point.

00:10:30.250 --> 00:10:35.520
I'm trying to be
mindful to everything

00:10:35.520 --> 00:10:41.563
that is happening in this body
mind combination every moment.

00:11:20.950 --> 00:11:25.770
While continuing to look
at the breathing in and out

00:11:25.770 --> 00:11:36.570
and while continuing to observe
how these sensory organs

00:11:36.570 --> 00:11:43.950
conduct themselves with regard
to external stimulation,

00:11:43.950 --> 00:11:48.830
see the impermanence
in the eyes,

00:11:48.830 --> 00:11:54.540
impermanence in the
objects that the eye sees.

00:11:54.540 --> 00:11:56.426
Impermanence in the
eye consciousness.

00:11:59.960 --> 00:12:02.830
Impermanence in the ears.

00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:05.830
Impermanence of the sound.

00:12:05.830 --> 00:12:07.836
Impermanence of the
sound consciousness.

00:12:10.680 --> 00:12:17.920
In this manner, the impermanence
of every sensory organ,

00:12:17.920 --> 00:12:22.160
including the mind,
the thoughts we get.

00:12:25.130 --> 00:12:35.540
In this body or mind, I
cannot discover anything

00:12:35.540 --> 00:12:37.065
as a permanent entity.

00:12:44.640 --> 00:12:46.925
Everything changes every moment.

00:12:52.010 --> 00:13:01.340
I shall attempt to abstain from
holding to anything material

00:13:01.340 --> 00:13:05.485
or mental with attachment.

00:13:11.130 --> 00:13:18.085
I know that attachment
brings suffering, sorrow.

00:13:27.820 --> 00:13:31.420
Now with that observation
of mindfulness of the body

00:13:31.420 --> 00:13:40.670
and mind-- body, sensations,
perceptions, relations,

00:13:40.670 --> 00:13:41.420
and consciousness.

00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:57.360
So these five, they
see as momentary

00:13:57.360 --> 00:14:03.640
of momentary existence
and attachment

00:14:03.640 --> 00:14:06.695
is not going to
be of any benefit.

00:14:09.720 --> 00:14:14.490
The same process takes
place in all of us.

00:14:14.490 --> 00:14:18.340
For first I extend loving
kindness to my own body

00:14:18.340 --> 00:14:25.140
and mind, then I extend
loving kindness to all of us

00:14:25.140 --> 00:14:28.520
present here.

00:14:28.520 --> 00:14:32.690
Then let us extend our
loving kindness to all those

00:14:32.690 --> 00:14:35.100
who are near and dear to us.

00:14:35.100 --> 00:14:39.450
Our parents, our spouses,
our children, our friends,

00:14:39.450 --> 00:14:42.010
our colleagues.

00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:43.805
May all of them
be well and happy.

00:14:46.590 --> 00:14:50.900
May we now extend
the loving kindness

00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:54.590
to everybody on this compound.

00:14:54.590 --> 00:14:59.720
Everybody in this area,
everybody in our country,

00:14:59.720 --> 00:15:02.380
everybody in this world.

00:15:02.380 --> 00:15:06.400
From mindfulness of
my own body and mind

00:15:06.400 --> 00:15:12.130
and realizing its impermanence
and detaching myself

00:15:12.130 --> 00:15:17.580
and reducing my egoism, I
extend my loving kindness

00:15:17.580 --> 00:15:21.820
to the entire living
world, entire universe.

00:15:26.330 --> 00:15:31.040
With mindfulness we
began, with loving

00:15:31.040 --> 00:15:33.115
kindness we expanded our hearts.

00:15:36.910 --> 00:15:41.780
It's going to create a critical
mass of spiritual consciousness

00:15:41.780 --> 00:15:49.310
in the world without which
there is no peace possible.

00:15:49.310 --> 00:15:51.970
Without which we
can't put an end

00:15:51.970 --> 00:15:55.990
to enmity, hunger, conflicts.

00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:01.750
May I be well and happy.

00:16:01.750 --> 00:16:05.100
May all of us be well and happy.

00:16:05.100 --> 00:16:07.120
May the entire world
be well and happy.

00:16:29.290 --> 00:16:30.460
Thank you.

00:16:30.460 --> 00:16:34.030
DR. WALTER LINK: Before
you open your eyes,

00:16:34.030 --> 00:16:40.850
please notice the impact
that this practice has

00:16:40.850 --> 00:16:43.940
had on your mind and your head.

00:16:47.440 --> 00:16:53.620
Not only the thoughts, but
also the energy, the space,

00:16:53.620 --> 00:16:57.520
the quality of
experience in your head.

00:17:08.030 --> 00:17:13.219
And then notice also the
impact on your feelings.

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:24.990
Internally, without
speaking them,

00:17:24.990 --> 00:17:32.375
find a few words that describe
your inner state of feeling.

00:17:46.490 --> 00:17:51.320
And then notice also your
belly and the rest of your body

00:17:51.320 --> 00:17:53.990
and the sensations
you have there.

00:18:04.360 --> 00:18:07.055
Notice that the breath
is flowing in the belly.

00:18:13.890 --> 00:18:17.710
Kind of anchor yourself in
this awareness of the breath

00:18:17.710 --> 00:18:29.090
in the belly, and then
gently, without rushing,

00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:36.260
allow your eyes to
open while remaining

00:18:36.260 --> 00:18:37.710
focused in your belly.

00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:49.690
Notice that it can be quite
challenging because the eyes

00:18:49.690 --> 00:18:52.130
bring in powerful
sensations that

00:18:52.130 --> 00:18:54.730
pull us towards the sensation.

00:18:58.760 --> 00:19:08.140
And rather let what you
see come to you so that you

00:19:08.140 --> 00:19:11.650
see what you see and
hear what you hear

00:19:11.650 --> 00:19:17.695
and it enters the space of
you that includes your body.

00:19:22.890 --> 00:19:27.650
And you keep noticing the
impact that it has there.

00:19:37.980 --> 00:19:44.110
In a moment we will
go into much more

00:19:44.110 --> 00:19:49.200
content for the mind, that the
mind hopefully will get curious

00:19:49.200 --> 00:19:54.240
about and engaged
with, and we spend

00:19:54.240 --> 00:19:57.460
a lot of time in
our head center,

00:19:57.460 --> 00:19:59.386
thinking and being inspired.

00:19:59.386 --> 00:20:06.430
And it's also good to
keep present in your belly

00:20:06.430 --> 00:20:07.535
and in your heart center.

00:20:11.180 --> 00:20:18.310
And notice how you're impacted
as we speak in an ongoing way.

00:20:18.310 --> 00:20:24.290
Because often we
think that listening

00:20:24.290 --> 00:20:29.140
is to pay attention to
the other and especially

00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:30.060
to the other's words.

00:20:33.200 --> 00:20:35.190
And that's really
important also.

00:20:39.990 --> 00:20:42.870
But, really, our
heart and our body

00:20:42.870 --> 00:20:45.285
is constantly also
being impacted.

00:20:48.090 --> 00:20:55.470
And the more awareness we have
about this impact in ourselves

00:20:55.470 --> 00:20:58.730
by the other, the
more freedom of choice

00:20:58.730 --> 00:21:00.750
we have how to respond.

00:21:05.310 --> 00:21:10.890
And so this is a way how you
can take this ancient Buddhist

00:21:10.890 --> 00:21:16.470
practice into really every
moment of your life--

00:21:16.470 --> 00:21:22.880
in a business meeting, in
a strategy and innovation

00:21:22.880 --> 00:21:23.380
discussion.

00:21:25.950 --> 00:21:30.670
We can stay present
to ourselves and see

00:21:30.670 --> 00:21:33.820
that there are different
parts of ourselves impacted

00:21:33.820 --> 00:21:40.780
and that also the other
person is not only their words

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:46.600
but they might have certain
feelings, a certain presence

00:21:46.600 --> 00:21:52.040
that's also really an
important way they communicate.

00:21:52.040 --> 00:21:54.780
So it's really a unity.

00:21:54.780 --> 00:22:00.330
There's you and me in this
mutual impact that we have.

00:22:00.330 --> 00:22:03.220
And when we open
that even further,

00:22:03.220 --> 00:22:07.010
then we see that there's
a whole field here,

00:22:07.010 --> 00:22:10.000
because we will all
impact each other.

00:22:10.000 --> 00:22:13.520
And of course there's the whole
company and the whole world.

00:22:13.520 --> 00:22:19.600
And we can listen, use
this mindfulness to really

00:22:19.600 --> 00:22:25.120
be aware of what's going on
on these different levels

00:22:25.120 --> 00:22:31.710
and keep coming back to that
during our time together.

00:22:31.710 --> 00:22:35.690
Just to practice
together and not only

00:22:35.690 --> 00:22:37.360
talk about interesting stuff.

00:22:41.390 --> 00:22:42.954
So with that, I
pass it on to you.

00:22:42.954 --> 00:22:43.495
MALE SPEAKER:

00:22:43.495 --> 00:22:45.130
Thank you, my friends.

00:22:45.130 --> 00:22:47.950
Dr. Ari, my first
question is for you.

00:22:47.950 --> 00:22:51.650
So you started as an
English in college

00:22:51.650 --> 00:22:55.570
and you ended up with
a huge social movement.

00:22:55.570 --> 00:22:57.299
So my first question is, how?

00:22:57.299 --> 00:22:58.590
What was the story behind this?

00:22:59.895 --> 00:23:04.000
DR. A.T. ARIYARATNE:
While I was a teacher,

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:13.080
my hobby or pastime was to
visit communities, particularly

00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:18.200
those that were socially and
economically very depressed

00:23:18.200 --> 00:23:20.640
communities.

00:23:20.640 --> 00:23:26.550
And then one day in my class,
consisting of teenagers,

00:23:26.550 --> 00:23:29.110
I told them the
story of one village.

00:23:29.110 --> 00:23:32.110
I said I visited many villages.

00:23:32.110 --> 00:23:34.720
The more I visited these
village communities,

00:23:34.720 --> 00:23:41.220
the more I feel that there
are things that we as students

00:23:41.220 --> 00:23:46.806
also can do without
waiting until we grow up

00:23:46.806 --> 00:23:50.290
and take various
kinds of employment.

00:23:50.290 --> 00:23:56.320
Then my students suggested, why
don't we organize ourselves,

00:23:56.320 --> 00:23:59.640
do it in the next vacation,
go to a village live

00:23:59.640 --> 00:24:05.300
with the village people, learn
from them while contributing

00:24:05.300 --> 00:24:09.370
to some-- contributing
in some way

00:24:09.370 --> 00:24:14.760
or other to satisfy one or
more of their basic needs,

00:24:14.760 --> 00:24:20.030
That's how it all
started 56 years ago.

00:24:20.030 --> 00:24:24.380
So all these students
and teachers, all of us,

00:24:24.380 --> 00:24:27.770
settled down in the village
for a couple of weeks,

00:24:27.770 --> 00:24:31.310
and we asked village people
that we will cook together

00:24:31.310 --> 00:24:32.700
in one kitchen.

00:24:32.700 --> 00:24:33.730
We will eat together.

00:24:33.730 --> 00:24:36.070
We will sing together.

00:24:36.070 --> 00:24:37.750
We'll meditate together.

00:24:37.750 --> 00:24:41.060
We'll dance together
at the same time.

00:24:41.060 --> 00:24:43.750
We will share our
labor and whatever

00:24:43.750 --> 00:24:48.240
skills we have to build a
well, to build a school,

00:24:48.240 --> 00:24:50.390
to build some toilets.

00:24:50.390 --> 00:24:55.290
Do some agriculture
work like that.

00:24:55.290 --> 00:24:56.690
So we had a timetable.

00:24:56.690 --> 00:25:02.960
We are, during two weeks' time,
a physical acheivements of work

00:25:02.960 --> 00:25:08.960
was there which anybody
could see, feel, physically.

00:25:08.960 --> 00:25:15.940
At the same time, we had
about four hours or more

00:25:15.940 --> 00:25:21.960
of meditation, discussion,
learning from one another.

00:25:21.960 --> 00:25:29.180
So it began a kind of
educational extension program,

00:25:29.180 --> 00:25:32.410
which continued
to other villages,

00:25:32.410 --> 00:25:36.900
during other vacations
and weekends.

00:25:36.900 --> 00:25:44.930
Then we found ourselves that we
were a big village development

00:25:44.930 --> 00:25:45.930
movement.

00:25:45.930 --> 00:25:51.650
So we have to organize ourselves
from education to development.

00:25:51.650 --> 00:25:54.230
And development
actually was a word

00:25:54.230 --> 00:25:58.292
which was meant for animals--
livestock development and all

00:25:58.292 --> 00:25:59.080
that.

00:25:59.080 --> 00:26:02.860
But I think it was one of
the American presidential--

00:26:02.860 --> 00:26:07.920
gave development the connotation
that human beings should

00:26:07.920 --> 00:26:09.460
be developed.

00:26:09.460 --> 00:26:13.140
In a way, he was right,
because we have degenerated,

00:26:13.140 --> 00:26:17.780
most of us, into the
worst of human animals.

00:26:17.780 --> 00:26:19.550
Otherwise, these
killings can't go on.

00:26:19.550 --> 00:26:23.000
This exploitation can't
go on in the world.

00:26:23.000 --> 00:26:25.020
But we give a different
meaning to development.

00:26:25.020 --> 00:26:28.750
We said it's an
awakening process.

00:26:28.750 --> 00:26:34.530
We have come to this village to
awaken our human personality.

00:26:34.530 --> 00:26:38.780
And in our culture, in
the Buddhist teachings,

00:26:38.780 --> 00:26:43.340
we have been told that
there are four principles,

00:26:43.340 --> 00:26:48.330
very simple to remember, which
could be practised by all of us

00:26:48.330 --> 00:26:52.900
at all times to awaken
our personality at work,

00:26:52.900 --> 00:26:55.970
when we take a
bath, when we eat.

00:26:55.970 --> 00:26:59.000
Whatever we do during the day.

00:26:59.000 --> 00:27:01.530
First is loving kindness.

00:27:01.530 --> 00:27:07.770
So we practiced this meta
mediation, meditation

00:27:07.770 --> 00:27:14.160
on loving kindness,
trying to as much

